0.user_question: Sam was collecting cans for recycling. On Saturday he filled 3 bags up and on Sunday he filled 4 more bags. If each bag had 9 cans in it, how many cans did he pick up total?

ost_step.1: Find out how many bags Sam filled up on Saturday. Each bag holds 9 cans, so the number of cans Sam picked up on Saturday is 3 bags * 9 cans/bag = 27 cans.
ost_step.2: Find out how many bags he filled up on Sunday. Since he filled 4 more bags than he did on Saturday, then he filled 7 bags in total (3 bags on Saturday + 4 bags on Sunday). So, he picked up 7 bags * 9 cans/bag = 63 cans on Sunday.
ost_step.3: Find out the total number of cans Sam collected. The total number of cans is the sum of the number of cans he collected on Saturday and Sunday. So, the total number of cans is 27 cans (on Saturday) + 63 cans (on Sunday) = 90 cans.
